summary: This is an email chain from July 2019 discussing logistical coordination for FBI interviews with potential victims of Jeffrey Epstein in West Palm Beach, Florida. It involves FBI personnel and a victim services coordinator arranging availability to meet with victims after their interviews.

keyFacts: FBI interviews with potential Epstein victims were actively scheduled in West Palm Beach, Florida, on July 11, 2019.
A victim services coordinator was on standby to meet with victims immediately after their FBI interviews to provide support.
The email chain highlights the ongoing federal investigation into Epstein's activities in July 2019, shortly before his arrest.
The communication shows coordination between the FBI case agent and support personnel regarding victim logistics.
